The Lagos State Government said it would divert traffic on Awolowo Way between Ikeja Under Bridge and Simbiat Abiola Way from noon on Saturdayto 6.00 am next Monday. A statement by Dr. Frederic Oladeinde, Commissioner for Transportation, Lagos State, said that the diversion was to enable junction improvement works by the government. Oladeinde explained that the traffic diversion was necessary to facilitate the delivery of the junction improvement works at record time, and assured of safety of motorists within the period. BREAKING: Traffic Diverted As Fuel Tanker Falls At Airport Road March 9 Polls: INECâ€™s Sensitive Materials Arrive Ekiti The commissioner explained that an adequate traffic management plan has been put in place for the period of the diversion, adding that motorists inbound Awolowo Way from the General Hospital Ikeja or Airport Road would be diverted to Oba Akran through Ikeja Underbridge. He also said that the motorists could make a turn at Allen Junction to Ajao Street by the Lagoon Hospital to link Adeniyi Jones and connect with Oba Akran to further their journey. He stressed that Aromire Road would also be opened to motorists as an alternative. Besides, Oladeinde explained that motorists inbound Ikeja Under Bridge from Simbiat Abiola Way heading towards Adeniyi Jones and other areas in Ikeja would be diverted to Akinremi Street to link Oshifila Street and Abeokuta Street to access Oba Akran for their desired destinations. He assured that the Lagos State Traffic Management Authority (LASTMA) personnel would be on the ground to control traffic, but further appealed to residents and motorists in the area to cooperate with government and its representatives for the work to be completed at the stipulated time.